qas.question: A mammal's brain is how many times larger than a birds relative to body size?
A mammal's brain is how many times larger than a reptiles relative to body size?
The biggest difference between brains of mammals and other vertebrates is what?

context: The most obvious difference between the brains of mammals and other vertebrates is in terms of <a2_0>size.<a2_0/> On average, a mammal has a brain roughly <a0_0>twice as large<a0_0/> as that of a bird of the same body size, and <a1_0>ten times<a1_0/> as large as that of a reptile of the same body size.
